248%2FUntitled-design-4.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20where%20data%20has%20become%20the%20dominant%20marker%20of%20economic%20prowess%2C%20any%20promulgation%20of%20legislation%20in%20this%20domain%20warrants%20meticulousness%20and%20circumspection%2C%20apart%20from%20having%20a%20far-sighted%20perspective.%20When%20British%20mathematician%20Clive%20Humby%20declared%20%E2%80%98data%20as%20the%20new%20oil%E2%80%99%20in%202006%2C%20he%20himself%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20foreseen%20the%20pervasive%20impact.%20Unlike%20oil%2C%20data%20is%20something%20that%20can%20be%20used%20and%20reused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%2C%20we%20wish%20to%20raise%20a%20pertinent%20question%20and%20then%20separate%20the%20truth%20from%20the%20tsunami%20of%20hype%20created%20around%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%20by%20looking%20closely%20at%20multiple%20issues%20of%20concern%20that%20have%20unfortunately%20been%20swept%20under%20the%20carpet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20a%20balancing%20Act%20or%20a%20disquieting%20retreat%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20hasty%20sweeping%20stride%2C%20the%20government%20recently%20secured%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament%20without%20any%20meaningful%20discussion.%20It%20got%20the%20assent%20of%20the%20president%20on%20August%2011%2C%202023%20%E2%80%93%20within%20two%20days%20of%20its%20passing%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20It%20is%20being%20touted%20as%20a%20landmark%20piece%20of%20legislation%20with%20the%20potential%20to%20redefine%20the%20contours%20of%20data%20governance%20in%20the%20contemporary%20digital%20landscape.%20Yet%2C%20beneath%20its%20professed%20intentions%20lies%20a%20labyrinth%20of%20clauses%20and%20provisions%20that%20warrant%20meticulous%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Act%20has%20ignited%20significant%20debate%20and%20concern%20amongst%20citizens%2C%20industry%20and%20experts%20alike.%20Although%20the%20legislation%20ostensibly%20seeks%20to%20safeguard%20individual%20privacy%20and%20data%20rights%2C%20a%20closer%20examination%20of%20its%20provisions%20unfurls%20pressing%20concerns%20about%20its%20efficacy%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20the%20potential%20reverberations%20of%20its%20implementation.%20This%20article%20is%20an%20earnest%20attempt%20to%20unravel%20the%20ramifications%20of%20this%20Act%2C%20primarily%20focusing%20on%20the%20pivotal%20aspects%20of%20%E2%80%98delegated%20legislation%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Data%20Protection%20Board%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Voluntary%20Undertaking%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Reasonable%20Security%20Safeguards%2C%E2%80%99%20dilution%20of%20Data%20Fiduciary%C2%A0and%20Data%20Processor%C2%A0responsibilities%2C%20transgressions%20against%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%20and%20an%20assortment%20of%20exemptions%20it%20confers%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20its%20commitment%20to%20safeguarding%20individual%20rights%20and%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExcessive%20reliance%20on%20delegated%20legislation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelegated%20legislation%20grants%20considerable%20discretion%20to%20various%20administrative%20agencies%20which%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20lead%20to%20rampant%20abuse%20or%20the%20exercise%20of%20excessive%20power.%20Under%20the%20pretext%20of%20making%20the%20legislation%20lean%2C%20the%20Government%20has%20deliberately%20laid%20this%20piece%20of%20legislation%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20subordinate%20agencies.%20In%20the%20dissenting%20judgment%20in%20the%20verdict%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20demonetisation%2C%20Justice%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20reminded%20us%20that%20unguided%20and%20unlimited%20powers%20under%20delegation%20would%20be%20%3Cem%3Eex%C2%AD-facie%3C%2Fem%3E%20arbitrary%20and%20suffer%20from%20the%20vice%20of%20unconstitutionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%E2%80%99s%20over-reliance%20on%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20clarity%20and%20specificity%20in%20its%20provisions.%20There%20is%20excessive%20delegated%20legislation%2C%20as%20the%20legislation%20does%20not%20largely%20go%20into%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20implementation.%20It%20seems%20as%20if%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20catchphrase%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20highlight%20of%20this%20DPDP%20Act.%20It%20has%20been%20used%2028%20times%20in%20a%2021-page%20Act%20with%2044%20sections.%20The%20ambiguity%20has%20been%20kept%20so%20that%20the%20government%20can%20take%20arbitrary%20decisions.%20No%20legislation%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20sound%20proof%20if%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20clauses%20are%20termed%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98as%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%99%20provision.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20the%20liberty%20of%20the%20government%2C%20that%20is%20executive%2C%20to%20take%20the%20decision%20at%20its%20convenience.%20This%20not%20only%20erodes%20the%20transparency%20of%20the%20legislative%20process%20but%20also%20undermines%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20understand%20the%20scope%20and%20implications%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Law%20Raises%20Questions%20About%20Consistency%20With%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20Ruling%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-law-raises-questions-about-consistency-with-right-to-privacy-ruling%5C%22%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Law%20Raises%20Questions%20About%20Consistency%20With%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20Ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStriking%20a%20discordant%20note%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pursuit%20of%20justice%20for%20aggrieved%20parties%20(sans%20compensation)%20requires%20recourse%20to%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%2C%20necessitating%20its%20independence.%20Yet%2C%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20permits%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20appoint%20the%20chairperson%20and%20board%20members%2C%20without%20specifying%20any%20selection%20procedure%2C%20undermining%20its%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20contradicts%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20the%202019%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%20which%20sought%20the%20nomination%20of%20board%20members%20by%20a%20Selection%20Committee%20comprising%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20bureaucrats%2C%20(i)%20Attorney%20General%20of%20India%2C%20(ii)%20an%20independent%20expert%20from%20fields%20such%20as%20data%20protection%2C%20information%20technology%2C%20or%20cyber%20laws%2C%20and%20(iii)%20Directors%20of%20an%20IIT%20and%20an%20IIM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20nature%20of%20independence%20of%20the%20Board%20is%20scuttled%20with%20this%20arbitrary%20nature%20of%20appointment.%20This%20latitude%20in%20appointment%20curtails%20the%20Board%E2%80%99s%20autonomy%2C%20resonating%20discordantly%20with%20the%20principle%20of%20an%20independent%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVoluntary%20undertaking%3A%20a%20haven%20for%20delinquents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20is%20Section%2032%2C%20which%20introduces%20a%20perplexing%20paradigm%20of%20%E2%80%98Voluntary%20Undertaking.%E2%80%99%20The%20provision%20bestows%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20with%20the%20authority%20to%20accept%20voluntary%20undertakings%20from%20those%20in%20non-compliance%20with%20the%20Act%E2%80%99s%20provisions%20and%20to%20stop%20further%20enquiry.%20The%20true%20import%20of%20this%20provision%20is%20not%20in%20its%20apparent%20benign%20essence%2C%20but%20in%20the%20potential%2C%20it%20holds%20to%20provide%20a%20cloak%20for%20delinquents%20to%20sidestep%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20offenders%20can%20dodge%20fines%20up%20to%20a%20staggering%20Rs%20250%20crore%20per%20offence%20by%20giving%20a%20mere%20undertaking%2C%20thus%20nullifying%20the%20deterrent%20essence%20of%20the%20legislation.%20By%20enabling%20data%20fiduciaries%20to%20escape%20penalties%20for%20non-compliance%2C%20the%20legislation%20unwittingly%20forges%20a%20let-out%20clause%20that%20could%20potentially%20be%20exploited%20by%20those%20with%20unscrupulous%20intent.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20could%20dilute%20the%20accountability%20ethos%20of%20the%20Act%20and%20result%20in%20inadequate%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvasion%20of%20compensation%20and%20accountability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20glaring%20lacuna%20is%20the%20absence%20of%20provision%20for%20awarding%20compensation%20by%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20to%20aggrieved%20data%20principals.%20While%20penalties%20can%20be%20imposed%20by%20the%20Board%20on%20data%20fiduciaries%20for%20contravening%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Act%2C%20which%20goes%20to%20the%20Consolidated%20Fund%20of%20India%20as%20per%20section%2034%2C%20it%20is%20not%20equipped%20with%20the%20power%20to%20award%20any%20compensation%20to%20the%20aggrieved%20Data%20Principals.%20This%20deficiency%20hampers%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20the%20legislation%20in%20redressing%20actual%20harm%20suffered%20by%20individuals%20resulting%20from%20data%20breaches%20or%20privacy%20infringements.%20Curiously%2C%20the%20Act%20stipulates%20penalties%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%2C000%20for%20Data%20Principals%20for%20non-observance%20of%20certain%20provisions%20of%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20compensatory%20measures%20reflects%20a%20lopsided%20emphasis%20on%20purported%20punitive%20actions%20rather%20than%20restorative%20justice%2C%20a%20scenario%20that%20is%20particularly%20hard%20to%20swallow%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20aforementioned%20%E2%80%98voluntary%20undertaking%E2%80%99%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUncharted%20waters%20of%20reasonable%20security%20safeguards%20and%20transgressions%20to%20IT%20Act%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20sub-section%20(5)%20of%20section%208%20of%20the%20Act%20purports%20to%20grant%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20the%20potential%20to%20proceed%20against%20a%20Data%20Fiduciary%20for%20breaches%20of%20their%20obligation%20to%20implement%20%E2%80%98reasonable%20security%20safeguards%E2%80%99%20against%20personal%20data%20breaches%2C%20with%20the%20power%20to%20impose%20a%20penalty%20up%20to%20Rs%20250%20crores%2C%20it%20falters%20in%20expounding%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98reasonable%20security%20safeguards%E2%80%99.%20This%20paucity%20of%20clarity%20engenders%20room%20for%20interpretation%20and%20potential%20misuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%20refrains%20from%20defining%20the%20contours%20of%20reasonable%20security%20safeguards%20and%20from%20imposing%20a%20responsibility%20upon%20the%20Government%20to%20delineate%20it%20at%20least%20by%20way%20of%20Rules.%20This%20absence%20may%20beget%20a%20veneer%20of%20compliance%2C%20wherein%20entities%20could%20manipulate%20trivial%20safeguards%20to%20evade%20liability.%20How%20can%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20arrive%20at%20a%20finding%20of%20committing%20failure%20by%20a%20data%20fiduciary%20in%20taking%20reasonable%20security%20safeguards%20in%20an%20instance%20of%20personal%20data%20breach%2C%20when%20the%20legislation%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20define%20the%20same%3F%20The%20transformation%20of%20%E2%80%98reasonable%20security%20safeguards%E2%80%99%20into%20an%20obscure%20abstraction%20dilutes%20the%20assurance%20of%20data%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20artful%20manipulation%20is%20further%20underscored%20by%20the%20Act%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20to%20omit%20sections%2043A%20and%2087(2)(ob)%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000.%20Section%2044(2)%20(a)%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20is%20for%20obliterating%20section%2043A%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%202000.%20Section%2043(A)%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%202000%20enabled%20an%20affected%20person%20(Data%20Principal)%20to%20demand%20damages%20by%20way%20of%20compensation%20from%20a%20body%20corporate%20for%20any%20negligence%20in%20implementing%20and%20maintaining%20reasonable%20security%20practices%20and%20procedures%20while%20processing%2C%20dealing%20or%20handling%20any%20sensitive%20personal%20data%20or%20information%20in%20a%20computer%20resource%20which%20the%20said%20body%20corporate%20owns%2C%20controls%20or%20operates.%20Likewise%2C%20section%2044(2)%20(c)%20of%20the%20DPDP%20Act%20is%20for%20abrogating%20section%2087(2)(ob)%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20only%20provision%20which%20cast%20a%20duty%20upon%20the%20central%20government%20to%20prescribe%20by%20Rules%20what%20are%20the%20%E2%80%9Csensitive%20personal%20data%20or%20information%E2%80%9D%20and%20what%20are%20the%20%E2%80%9Creasonable%20security%20practices%20and%20procedures%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20followed%20by%20a%20body%20corporate%20while%20processing%2C%20dealing%20or%20handling%20any%20sensitive%20personal%20data%20or%20information%20in%20a%20computer%20resource%20which%20it%20owns%2C%20controls%20or%20operates%20%E2%80%93%20against%20the%20breach%20of%20which%20an%20affected%20party%20(Data%20Principal)%20can%20demand%20compensation%20from%20a%20body%20corporate%20under%20section%2043A%20of%20the%20IT%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22When%20'Data%20Protection'%20Undermines%20People%E2%80%99s%20Protection%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhen-data-protection-undermines-peoples-protection%5C%22%3EWhen%20%E2%80%98Data%20Protection%E2%80%99%20Undermines%20People%E2%80%99s%20Protection%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20not%20only%20does%20the%20government%20prevent%20a%20data%20principal%20from%20seeking%20compensation%20for%20data%20breach%20under%20this%20DPDP%20Act%2C%20but%20also%20clandestinely%20succeeded%20in%20removing%20the%20two%20enabling%20provisions%20from%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%20%E2%80%93%20killing%20three%20birds%20with%20one%20stone!%20By%20quashing%20the%20provisions%20in%20IT%20Act%2C%20the%20Act%20curbs%20the%20avenues%20for%20affected%20parties%20to%20seek%20compensation%20for%20data%20breaches%20and%20accentuates%20their%20precarious%20situation%2C%20setting%20a%20trajectory%20that%20contrasts%20with%20the%20European%20Union%E2%80%99s%20General%20Data%20Protection%20Regulation%20(GDPR)%2C%20which%20robustly%20provides%20for%20right%20to%20compensation%20for%20breach%20of%20personal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymphony%20of%20exemptions%20and%20accountability%20erosion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20conspicuous%20vulnerability%20looms%20in%20the%20mosaic%20of%20exemptions%20strewn%20across%20the%20Act.%20Section%2017%20grants%20the%20Union%20government%20carte%20blanche%20to%20exempt%20government%20agencies%20and%20data%20fiduciaries%2C%20including%20start-ups%2C%20from%20various%20provisions.%20The%20blanket%20dispensation%20to%20government%20agencies%2C%20ostensibly%20anchored%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Einterests%20of%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20State%2C%20friendly%20relations%20with%20foreign%20States%2C%20maintenance%20of%20public%20order%20or%20preventing%20incitement%20to%20any%20cognizable%20offence%20relating%20to%20any%20of%20these%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eposes%20queries%20about%20the%20unbridled%20exercise%20of%20executive%20power%20and%20can%20result%20in%20undue%20infringement%20of%20privacy%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisproportionate%20exemptions%20for%20government%20entities%20might%20inadvertently%20facilitate%20the%20sidestepping%20of%20data%20protection%20mandates%2C%20eroding%20the%20legislation%E2%80%99s%20core%20intent.%20Besides%2C%20the%20wide-ranging%20powers%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20exempt%20data%20fiduciaries%20or%20classes%20of%20data%20fiduciaries%20from%20various%20provisions%20of%20the%20Act%20has%20the%20potential%20for%20misuse%20and%20will%20jeopardise%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20the%20legislative%20edifice%2C%20allowing%20select%20entities%20to%20evade%20their%20responsibilities.%20Likewise%2C%20there%20is%20no%20bar%20for%20the%20government%20in%20operating%20the%20available%20data%2C%20whether%20digital%20or%20non-digital%2C%20which%20has%20been%20converted%20into%20the%20digital%20format%20and%20stored%20for%20any%20period%20of%20time.%20The%20data%20principals%20have%20no%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20be%20forgotten%E2%80%99%20in%20so%20far%20as%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20are%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETorpedoing%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%E2%80%99s%20impending%20effect%20on%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%20also%20merits%20close%20attention.%20Section%2044(3)%20of%20DPDP%20Act%20abrogates%20the%20essence%20of%20Section%208(1)(j)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%20effectively%20rendering%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20information%20exempt%20from%20the%20RTI%E2%80%99s%20purview.%20Erstwhile%20section%208(1)(j)%20of%20the%20RTI%20act%20allowed%20even%20personal%20information%20to%20be%20disclosed%20if%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%20justifies%20the%20disclosure%20of%20such%20information%20or%20it%20is%20related%20to%20any%20public%20activity%20or%20interest%3B%20even%20if%20the%20disclosure%20causes%20unwarranted%20invasion%20of%20the%20privacy%20of%20the%20individual%2C%20and%20further%20insists%20that%20all%20personal%20information%20shall%20be%20provided%20if%20it%20is%20such%20an%20information%20which%20cannot%20be%20denied%20to%20the%20Parliament%20or%20a%20State%20Legislature.%20This%20has%20been%20obliterated%20in%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%20thereby%20making%20all%20personal%20information%20exempt%20from%20disclosure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20would%20be%20that%20the%20Public%20Information%20Officers%20can%20reject%20a%20substantial%20number%20of%20RTI%20applications%2C%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20personal%20information%2C%20if%20they%20desire%20so.%20This%20ominous%20change%20would%20fundamentally%20weaken%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20threaten%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20in%20governance%2C%20curtailing%20public%20access%20to%20information%20and%20eroding%20the%20very%20bedrock%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EErosion%20of%20data%20processor%20accountability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%E2%80%99s%20propensity%20to%20dilute%20data%20processor%20accountability%20is%20conspicuous.%20In%20its%20previous%20iteration%20as%20the%202022%20Bill%2C%20data%20processors%20were%20equally%20responsible%20for%20safeguarding%20personal%20data%20and%20notifying%20data%20breaches%20to%20the%20Board%20and%20Data%20Principals.%20However%2C%20the%202023%20Act%20eschews%20this%20obligation%2C%20potentially%20enabling%20data%20processors%2C%20often%20foreign%20conglomerates%2C%20to%20elude%20direct%20legal%20repercussions%20for%20data%20breaches.%20This%20shift%20towards%20appeasing%20favouritism%20compromises%20the%20accountability%20of%20data%20processors%20in%20safeguarding%20personal%20data%20and%20undermines%20the%20principle%20of%20shared%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDilution%20of%20liability%20for%20data%20sharing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20as%20per%20the%202022%20Bill%2C%20a%20data%20fiduciary%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20lapses%2Fwrong%20actions%20of%20another%20data%20fiduciary%20with%20whom%20they%20share%20data.%20This%20has%20been%20dropped%20in%20the%202023%20Act.%20This%20change%20attenuates%20the%20accountability%20framework%20and%20reduces%20the%20incentive%20for%20data%20fiduciaries%20to%20ensure%20proper%20handling%20and%20watchful%20sharing%20of%20personal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EData%20principal%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202023%20Act%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20either%20make%20it%20obligatory%20for%20data%20fiduciaries%20to%20obtain%20consent%20from%20data%20principals%20before%20sharing%20data%20with%20other%20data%20fiduciaries%20or%20data%20processors.%20This%20compromises%20data%20principals%E2%80%99%20authority%20over%20their%20personal%20data%20and%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20uninformed%20and%20uncontrolled%20sharing%20of%20personal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20the%202023%20Act%20no%20longer%20requires%20local%20storage%20of%20data.%20Businesses%20can%20transfer%20data%20to%20those%20foreign%20countries%20which%20are%20not%20in%20the%20negative%20list%20to%20be%20notified%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20%E2%80%93%20what%20would%20be%20the%20criteria%20for%20such%20a%20negative%20listing%3F%20Can%20it%20be%20used%20as%20a%20leverage%20to%20exhort%20foreign%20countries%20to%20toe%20the%20line%20of%20the%20Union%20government%3F%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20stipulation%20for%20local%20data%20storage%20unfurls%20the%20spectre%20of%20data%20transference%20to%20foreign%20jurisdictions%20without%20well-defined%20criteria%2C%20necessitating%20introspection%20into%20diplomatic%20dynamics%20and%20the%20preservation%20of%20national%20interests.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Why%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Won't%20Stop%20Data%20Proliferation%20in%20Digital%20India%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdata-protection-bull-proliferation-digital-india%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Won%E2%80%99t%20Stop%20Data%20Proliferation%20in%20Digital%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20spectrum%20of%20ambiguities%2C%20omissions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DPDP%20Act%20introduces%20ambiguity%20in%20critical%20areas%20such%20as%20data%20portability%2C%20data%20storage%20requirements%20and%20processing%20of%20non-digital%20personal%20data.%20This%20inherent%20ambiguity%20opens%20the%20gateway%20to%20divergent%20interpretations%20and%20potential%20misuses%20of%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExemption%20for%20processing%20children%E2%80%99s%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Act%20proposes%20to%20introduce%20some%20protection%20for%20children%E2%80%99s%20data%20in%20section%209%2C%20it%20dilutes%20those%20objectives%20in%20the%20same%20breath%20by%20introducing%20exemptions%20thereon.%20Section%209(4)%20of%20the%20Act%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20declare%20any%20classes%20of%20Data%20Fiduciaries%20to%20be%20exempted%20from%20the%20general%20restrictions%20in%20processing%20children%E2%80%99s%20personal%20data%2C%20such%20as%20obtaining%20verifiable%20consent%20from%20the%20parent%2Fguardian%20of%20the%20child%2C%20not%20undertaking%20tracking%20or%20behavioural%20monitoring%20of%20children%20or%20targeted%20advertising%20directed%20at%20children%2C%20etc.%2C%20subject%20to%20such%20conditions%20as%20may%20be%20prescribed%20by%20Rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEqually%20alarming%20is%20section%209(5)%2C%20which%20permits%20the%20government%20to%20exempt%20any%20Data%20Fiduciary%20from%20the%20need%20to%20seek%20parental%20consent%20for%20processing%20personal%20data%20of%20specific%20age%20groups%20of%20children%20or%20to%20empower%20a%20data%20fiduciary%20to%20undertake%20tracking%20or%20behavioural%20monitoring%20of%20children%20or%20targeted%20advertising%20directed%20at%20children%2C%20if%20the%20government%20is%20satisfied%20that%20the%20history%20of%20data%20processing%20by%20that%20Data%20Fiduciary%20is%20verifiably%20safe.%20This%20raises%20concerns%20of%20potential%20tracking%2C%20behavioural%20monitoring%2C%20and%20targeted%20advertising%20directed%20at%20children%20without%20the%20knowledge%20or%20consent%20of%20their%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20unending%20exercise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20intricate%20web%20of%20exemptions%20casts%20a%20shadow%20over%20the%20Act%E2%80%99s%20integrity.%20Sections%207(b)%2C%207(c)%2C%207(e)%2C%20and%207(i)%20provide%20data%20fiduciaries%20broad%20leeway%20to%20process%20personal%20data%20for%20diverse%20purposes%2C%20often%20without%20explicit%20consent.%20This%20may%20inadvertently%20facilitate%20unwarranted%20surveillance%2C%20discrimination%20or%20coercion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExploitative%20use%20of%20Data%20by%20the%20State%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Section%207(b)%20and%207(c)%20grant%20broad%20permissions%20to%20Data%20Fiduciaries%20to%20process%20personal%20data%20for%20the%20State%20and%20its%20instrumentalities.%20While%20section%207(b)%20allows%20for%20the%20use%20of%20personal%20data%20for%20any%20government%20purpose%20without%20explicit%20consent%2C%20even%20by%20converting%20the%20non-digital%20data%20to%20digital%20form%20without%20the%20permission%20of%20the%20data%20principal%2C%20section%207(c)%20gives%20blanket%20permission%20for%20a%20Data%20Fiduciary%20to%20process%20any%20personal%20data%20for%20the%20State%20or%20any%20of%20its%20instrumentalities%20in%20the%20name%20of%20sovereignty%2C%20integrity%20or%20security%20of%20the%20state.%20These%20clauses%20can%20potentially%20be%20exploited%20for%20surveillance%20and%20manipulation%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20governmental%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBypassing%20Legal%20Procedures%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Section%207(e)%20enables%20Data%20Fiduciaries%20to%20process%20personal%20data%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20complying%20with%20foreign%20judgments%20or%20orders%20relating%20to%20contractual%20or%20civil%20claims%2C%20without%20the%20permission%20of%20Indian%20courts.%20This%20provision%20essentially%20circumvents%20the%20established%20legal%20framework%20in%20India%20for%20complying%20with%20foreign%20judgments%20through%20courts%20of%20competent%20jurisdiction%20in%20India%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20Act%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20due%20process.%20It%20provides%20for%20direct%20execution%20of%20foreign%20judgments%20without%20the%20permission%20of%20Indian%20courts%20%E2%80%93%20bypassing%20the%20Code%20of%20Civil%20Procedure%2C%201908%20%E2%80%93%20by%20circumventing%20the%20relevant%20provisions%20regarding%20the%20compliance%20of%20foreign%20judgments%20through%20courts%20of%20competent%20jurisdiction%20in%20India%20as%20discussed%20in%20sections%2013%2C14%20and%2044A%20r%2Fw%202(5)%20and%202(6)%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Civil%20Procedure%2C%201908.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEmployer%E2%80%99s%20power%20over%20employee%20data%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20Section%207(i)%20provides%20employers%20with%20the%20authority%20to%20process%20personal%20data%20for%20employment-related%20purposes%2C%20potentially%20compromising%20the%20privacy%20and%20rights%20of%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsence%20of%20data%20profiling%20protection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20clause%204(2)%20of%202022%20Bill%2C%20the%20foreign%20data%20processing%20of%20Indian%20persons%20in%20connection%20with%20%E2%80%98data%20profiling%E2%80%99%20was%20also%20envisaged%20to%20be%20brought%20under%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20legislation.%20Now%20this%20%E2%80%98profiling%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20dropped%20from%20section%203(b)%20of%20the%202023%20DPDP%20Act%2C%20thereby%20making%20this%20Act%20apply%20only%20to%20foreign%20data%20processing%20relating%20to%20activity%20of%20offering%20goods%20or%20services%20to%20data%20principals%20in%20India.%20Data%20processing%20relating%20to%20any%20profiling%20is%20also%20a%20crucial%20area%20and%20the%20omission%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20potential%20misuse%20of%20personal%20data%20for%20profiling%20and%20targeted%20marketing.%20This%20omission%20contradicts%20international%20trends%20and%20overlooks%20the%20significance%20of%20profiling%20in%20the%20modern%20digital%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExclusion%20of%20non-digital%20and%20anonymised%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20include%20non-digital%20personal%20data%2C%20anonymised%20data%2C%20and%20non-personal%20data%20within%20its%20ambit%20raises%20questions%20about%20the%20comprehensiveness%20of%20the%20legislation.%20Such%20exclusions%20contradict%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20committee%20on%20the%20previous%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202019%20and%20overlook%20potential%20privacy%20risks%20associated%20with%20these%20data%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsence%20of%20right%20to%20data%20portability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20include%20the%20right%20to%20data%20portability%20is%20a%20significant%20shortcoming%2C%20considering%20that%20the%202019%20version%20of%20the%20bill%2C%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20Report%20and%20international%20regulations%20such%20as%20the%20GDPR%20recognise%20this%20right.%20The%20absence%20of%20this%20provision%20limits%20users%E2%80%99%20authority%20over%20their%20own%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemoval%20of%20sensitive%20and%20critical%20data%20distinction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20remove%20the%20distinction%20between%20sensitive%20and%20critical%20personal%20data%20in%202023%20Act%20eliminates%20the%20need%20for%20enhanced%20protection%20for%20specific%20categories%20of%20personal%20data.%20This%20move%20dilutes%20the%20protection%20offered%20to%20sensitive%20information.%20The%20distinction%20between%20different%20categories%20of%20personal%20data%20was%20recommended%20by%20Justice%20B.%20N.%20Srikrishna%20and%20was%20included%20in%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202019%20and%20the%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20recommendations%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20all%20are%20now%20%E2%80%98digital%20personal%20data%E2%80%99%20and%20none%20have%20any%20proper%20protection%20or%20right%20for%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsence%20of%20provisions%20for%20compensation%20for%20harm%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Charm%20to%20data%20principal%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20Act%2C%20and%20instead%2C%20it%20focuses%20on%20protecting%20the%20%E2%80%9Crights%20of%20data%20principals%E2%80%9D%3B%20albeit%20the%20Act%20does%20not%20include%20provisions%20that%20enable%20data%20principals%20to%20seek%20compensation%20for%20infringements%20on%20their%20deemed%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20Bill%2C%20JPC%20Report%20on%202019%20Bill%20and%202022%20Bill%20had%20all%20defined%20%E2%80%98harm%E2%80%99.%20The%20DPDP%20Act%20ought%20to%20have%20included%20provisions%20delineating%20the%20types%20of%20%E2%80%9Charm%E2%80%9D%20to%20data%20principals%20on%20breach%20of%20personal%20data%2C%20the%20occurrence%20of%20which%20would%20provide%20%3Cem%3Elocus%20standi%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20a%20data%20principal%20in%20raising%20a%20claim%20for%20compensation%20by%20approaching%20Data%20Protection%20Board%2FAppellate%20Tribunal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20conundrum%20of%20individual%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20potential%20misuse%20of%20children%E2%80%99s%20data%20to%20granting%20excessive%20power%20to%20the%20State%2C%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%20falls%20short%20of%20ensuring%20comprehensive%20data%20protection.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20omission%20of%20critical%20elements%20such%20as%20the%20absence%20of%20definition%20of%20reasonable%20security%20safeguards%2C%20lack%20of%20provisions%20for%20compensation%2C%20and%20unfettered%20power%20of%20the%20government%20to%20grant%20a%20deluge%20of%20exemptions%20indicate%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20to%20create%20a%20robust%20framework%20for%20safeguarding%20individuals%E2%80%99%20digital%20rights.%20It%20brings%20forth%20a%20labyrinthine%20journey%2C%20one%20fraught%20with%20uncertainties%20and%20ambiguities.%20Its%20lack%20of%20specificity%2C%20clarity%20and%20accountability%20leave%20a%20trail%20of%20apprehensions%20impacting%20data%20principals%20and%20the%20broader%20data%20protection%20landscape%20in%20India.%20Striking%20a%20harmonious%20balance%20between%20individual%20rights%20and%20emerging%20digital%20exigencies%20remains%20an%20enduring%20challenge.%20The%20ambiguities%2C%20omissions%2C%20and%20exemptions%20within%20the%20Act%20may%20lead%20to%20inadequate%20enforcement%2C%20reduced%20accountability%2C%20and%20diminished%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20has%20been%20held%20to%20be%20sacrosanct%20to%20human%20existence%20and%20an%20inalienable%20facet%20of%20human%20dignity%20and%20autonomy.%20Recently%2C%20in%20the%20context%20of%20%E2%80%98Pegasus%E2%80%99%20surveillance%20software%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EThe%20right%20to%20privacy%20is%20directly%20infringed%20when%20there%20is%20surveillance%20or%20spying%20done%20on%20an%20individual%2C%20either%20by%20the%20State%20or%20by%20any%20external%20agency%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20widespread%20storage%20and%20collection%20of%20personal%20data%20of%20individuals%2C%20taken%20without%20consent%2C%20violates%20the%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20informational%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20unequivocally%20declared%20by%20the%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EJustice%20K.S%20Puttaswamy%20(Retd.)%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%20and%20Ors.%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20right%20to%20privacy%20is%20protected%20as%20an%20intrinsic%20part%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%20under%20Article%2021%20and%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20freedoms%20guaranteed%20by%20Part%20III%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThus%2C%20the%20onus%20lies%20on%20the%20Indian%20legal%20system%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20DPDP%20Act%202023%20withstands%20the%20scrutiny%20of%20judicial%20review%20and%20charts%20a%20course%20toward%20data%20sovereignty%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20marred%20by%20half-measures%20and%20veiled%20compromises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJohn%20Brittas%20is%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20and%20Aneesh%20Babu%20is%20a%20researcher.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693099844000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F06095248%2FUntitled-design-4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-lies-beneath-the-pr-blitz-on-the-new-data-protection-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ambiguities%2C%20omissions%20and%20exemptions%20in%20the%C2%A0Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%C2%A0will%20result%20in%20poor%20enforcement%2C%20encourage%20low%20accountability%20and%20diminish%20transparency.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-lies-beneath-the-pr-blitz-on-the-new-data-protection-act%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20indiscriminate%20devastation%20of%20Canada's%20raging%20wildfires%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693098689000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F54D8%2Fproduction%2F_130902712_canadafireengine.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66620230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fires%20in%20western%20Canada%20have%20burned%20homes%20and%20ripped%20up%20trees%2C%20laying%20them%20down%20%26quot%3Blike%20toothpicks%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66620230%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66620230.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%