n%20as%20I%20learnt%20from%20Dutt%20that%20not%20only%20was%20she%20not%20consulted%20for%20the%20episode%2C%20but%20she%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20formally%20credited%20and%20no%20formal%20consent%20or%20permission%20was%20sought%20to%20use%20her%20story%20as%20a%20basis%20for%20creating%20Menke%E2%80%99s%20character.%20Dutt%20wrote%20a%20dignified%20note%20congratulating%20Ghaywan%20for%20his%20revolutionary%20episode%20and%20rightfully%20demanding%20due%20credit%20for%20her%20story%20and%20written%20work%20as%20inspiration%20for%20the%20storyline%20of%20the%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20makers%20of%20the%20series%2C%20savarna%20producers%20and%20writers%2C%20collectively%20brought%20out%20a%20condescending%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fghaywan%2Fstatus%2F1692179195185770757%5C%22%3Estatement%20discrediting%20Dutt%E2%80%99s%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20they%20called%20%E2%80%98misleading%20claims%E2%80%99.%20In%20one%20of%20her%20interviews%2C%20Dutt%20sensitively%20pointed%20out%20the%20difference%20between%20Neeraj%20Ghaywan%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCv1oAewsNTS%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_web_copy_link%26igshid%3DMzRlODBiNWFlZA%3D%3D%5C%22%3Enote%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20acknowledged%20that%20she%20was%20the%20inspiration%20behind%20the%20%E2%80%98interview%E2%80%99%20part%20of%20the%20episode%2C%20versus%20the%20collective%20statement.%20There%20is%20a%20difference%2C%20Dutt%20said%2C%20when%20two%20oppressed%20caste%20folks%20engage%20with%20one%20another%20in%20a%20respectful%2C%20dignified%20way%20vis-a-vis%20power-wielding%20savarna%2C%20who%20essentially%20look%20down%20upon%20her%20original%20contribution.%20One%20can%20understand%20the%20burdens%20Ghaywan%20might%20carry%20in%20being%20the%20only%20Dalit%20in%20the%20mainstream%20industry%20full%20of%20savarna%20who%20claim%20to%20be%20allies%20but%20who%20also%20mean%20%E2%80%98business%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%20the%20makers%E2%80%99%20failure%20to%20give%20journalist%20and%20writer%20Dutt%20due%20credit%20for%20her%20story%20and%20book%20inspiring%20their%20portrayal%20of%20an%20assertive%20Dalit%20woman%20writer%20is%20emblematic%20of%20a%20longstanding%20systemic%20and%20epistemic%20injustice.%20Misappropriation%20of%20oppressed%20caste%20communities%E2%80%99%20narratives%20to%20forward%20one%E2%80%99s%20academic%20career%2C%20NGO%20funding%20and%20in%20recent%20years%20in%20the%20film%20industry%2C%20a%20race%20to%20look%20more%20diversity-aware%20and%20inclusive%20in%20dealing%20with%20creative%20subjects%20is%20being%20critiqued%20by%20vocal%20anti-caste%20activists%20and%20scholars.%20The%20fetishising%20and%20exoticising%20of%20oppressed%20communities%E2%80%99%20experiences%20is%20not%20new.%20In%20several%20films%20from%20yesteryears%20and%20contemporary%20times%2C%20a%20savarna%20protagonist%20will%20play%20a%20saviour%20to%20helpless%20Dalit%20victims.%20Yet%20rising%20global%20awareness%20of%20inequalities%20and%20a%20new%20global%20market%20for%20stories%20from%20the%20margin%20have%20pushed%20savarnas%20to%20delve%20into%20topics%20they%20have%20never%20engaged%20with%20deeply.%20But%20the%20question%20is%3A%20Are%20they%20capable%20of%20the%20retrospection%20and%20self-reflection%20needed%20to%20create%20stories%20of%20the%20marginalised%20with%20respect%20and%20ethical%20collaboration%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20certainly%20matters%20who%20owns%20the%20narrative%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20oppressed%20castes%20and%20indigenous%20communities%2C%20because%20their%20stories%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20represented%20in%20full%20honesty%20and%20respect%20by%20those%20who%20hold%20the%20power%20to%20publicise%20stories%20in%20the%20mass%20media.%20Yet%20it%20is%20not%20so%20much%20about%20whether%20only%20oppressed%20castes%20can%20represent%20their%20stories%20the%20best%3B%20it%20is%20about%20what%20intentions%20those%20in%20power%20have%20when%20they%20tell%20the%20stories%20of%20the%20oppressed.%20Do%20they%20have%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20oppressed%20communities%20at%20heart%3F%20How%20do%20people%20in%20the%20industry%20and%20researchers%20ensure%20that%20they%20have%20the%20point%20of%20view%20and%20narratives%20of%20the%20communities%20they%20wish%20to%20creatively%20engage%20with%3F%20They%20will%20have%20to%20question%20their%20privileged%20caste%20location%20and%20point%20of%20view%2C%20as%20uncomfortable%20and%20confronting%20as%20this%20task%20may%20be.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20face%20the%20fact%20that%20their%20standpoint%20is%20limited%20because%20they%20have%20not%20engaged%20with%20oppressed%20caste%20communities%20beyond%20a%20transactional%20master-servant%20relationship.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20unlearn%20this%20ingrained%20superiority%20to%20discover%20their%20own%20humanity%20and%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20oppressed%20caste%20communities%20in%20their%20full%20capacity%20as%20humans%2C%20flawed%20and%20complex.%20Not%20only%20helpless%20victims%20or%20currently%20trendy%20assertive%20activists%20but%20also%20your%20Raj%2C%20Rahul%20and%20Poo%20of%20commercial%20Bollywood%20films!%20Where%20are%20the%20Kambles%20in%20any%20Indian%20film%E2%80%99s%20narrative%3F%20Corrupt%20gullible%20constables%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20privileged%20caste%20makers%20will%20have%20to%20create%20content%20that%20speaks%20to%20the%20oppressed%20communities%20and%20not%20merely%20for%20the%20savarna%20gaze.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20go%20so%20deep%20in%20reflection%20as%20to%20find%20it%20problematic%20to%20embark%20on%20a%20creative%20project%20without%20representation%20of%20the%20community%20on%20their%20team%2C%20right%20from%20the%20research%20for%20the%20story%2C%20the%20writing%20part%20and%20casting.%20It%20is%20not%20sufficient%20to%20have%20a%20token%20representation%20of%20one%20talented%20director%20from%20within%20the%20community%2C%20who%20is%20anyway%20%E2%80%98low-hanging%20fruit%E2%80%99.%20He%20has%20made%20it%20there%20against%20the%20odds.%20What%20about%20those%20who%20are%20not%20able%20to%20enter%20due%20to%20savarna%20gatekeeping%3F%20The%20savarna%20filmmakers%20will%20have%20to%20put%20effort%20into%20looking%20for%20and%20creating%20more%20such%20representatives%20from%20the%20community%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20academia%2C%20research%20on%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20work%20took%20centre%20stage%20predominantly%20since%20the%201990s%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20assertive%20anti-caste%20counter%20public%20and%20their%20vernacular%20booklets%20and%20pamphlets%20which%20sustained%20the%20anti-caste%20discourse%20among%20the%20masses.%20It%20was%20not%20without%20struggle%20and%20backlash.%20In%20similar%20vain%20in%20Indian%20cinema%2C%20the%20works%20of%20Pa%20Ranjith%2C%20Mari%20Selvaraj%2C%20Nagraj%20Manjule%20from%20the%20regional%20film%20industry%20and%20Neeraj%20Ghaywan%20from%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20have%20forced%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20narrative.%20The%20commercial%20production%20houses%20and%20streaming%20services%20headed%20by%20privileged%20caste%20folks%20are%20merely%20aping%20these%20trends%2C%20purely%20for%20financial%20gains%2C%20to%20reach%20an%20untapped%20viewership%20from%20the%20margin%20and%20garner%20the%20label%20of%20being%20progressive%20from%20the%20global%20viewership.%20The%20priorities%20are%20clearly%20different.%20The%20regional%20directors%20and%20storytellers%20completely%20debunked%20how%20Indian%20cinema%20is%20made%20and%20they%20questioned%20the%20narratives%20and%20portrayals%20of%20heroes%20and%20anti-heroes.%20Their%20protagonists%20are%20complex%20people%2C%20creating%20new%20film%20genres.%20Forcing%20others%20to%20follow%20suit.%20This%20is%20an%20achievement%20and%20an%20example%20of%20how%20with%20assertion%20and%20creativity%2C%20oppressed%20caste%20communities%20have%20shifted%20the%20dominant%20narratives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOppressed%20caste%20communities%20who%20use%20multiple%20nomenclature%20to%20define%20themselves%2C%20are%20diverse%20groups%20of%20people%2C%20regionally%2C%20religiously%2C%20linguistically%2C%20by%20caste%20and%20class%20too.%20What%20ties%20them%20all%20together%20is%20that%20they%20have%20been%20part%20of%20and%20experienced%20two%20centuries%20of%20collective%20consciousness-raising%20movements%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20majority%20hail%20Babasaheb%20Ambedkar%20as%20their%20inspiration%2C%20and%20then%20you%20have%20regional%20revolutionaries%20who%20rejected%20the%20historical%20imposition%20of%20caste%20and%20stigma.%20In%20the%20South%2C%20you%20have%20Iyothee%20Thas%20who%20insisted%20on%20conversion%20to%20Buddhism%20and%20Periyar%20who%20called%20for%20the%20rejection%20of%20religion%20altogether.%20You%20have%20oppressed%20caste%20folks%20going%20into%20socialist-communist%20revolutions%20and%20you%20have%20people%20converting%20to%20Islam%2C%20Sikhism%20and%20Christianity.%20They%20all%20found%20their%20emancipation%20in%20different%20ways.%20Yet%20they%20have%20carved%20out%20a%20common%20identity%20despite%20regional%20and%20other%20differences%2C%20due%20to%20the%20movement%E2%80%99s%20solidarity%20and%20allyship%20over%20these%20centuries.%20It%20is%20far%20from%20perfect%20but%20my%20point%20is%20that%20these%20are%20complex%20groups%20of%20people%2C%20and%20they%20have%20unique%20narratives.%20As%20producers%20engaged%20in%20creating%20authentic%20stories%2C%20you%20will%20have%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20whether%20your%20story%20is%20inspired%20by%20thousands%20or%20an%20individual%20and%20how%20you%20make%20sure%20that%20while%20you%20draw%20inspiration%20from%20the%20narratives%20of%20thousands%20to%20create%20one%20character%2C%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20erase%20unique%20individual%20stories%20that%20have%20aided%20your%20creative%20process.%20It%20is%20your%20ethical%20obligation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20communities%20across%20India%20who%20experience%20caste%20oppression%2C%20did%20not%20have%20the%20privilege%20of%20the%20anti-caste%20movement.%20They%20lived%20in%20close%20proximity%20to%20their%20oppressors%20in%20towns%20and%20villages.%20Coming%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98Bhangi%E2%80%99%20community%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20one%20can%20only%20imagine%20the%20ordeals%20Dutt%E2%80%99s%20family%20went%20through.%20The%20violence%20of%20not%20disclosing%20one%E2%80%99s%20oppressed%20identity%2C%20living%20in%20hiding%2C%20all%20this%20Dutt%20describes%20in%20her%20book%2C%20which%20I%20suggest%20everyone%20should%20read.%20This%20is%20a%20form%20of%20oppression.%20Her%20grandmother%20cleaned%20human%20excreta%20in%20remote%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20approximately%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20my%20grandfather%20whipped%20himself%20and%20begged%20for%20alms%20as%20a%20Potraj%20in%20remote%20Maharashtra%20carrying%20the%20goddess%E2%80%99s%20temple%20on%20his%20head.%20Dutt%E2%80%99s%20grandfather%20got%20educated%20somehow%20and%20my%20grandfather%20inspired%20by%20Ambedkar%20came%20to%20the%20city%2C%20to%20toil%20and%20labour%20in%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20grandfather%20was%20a%20staunch%20Ambedkarite%20who%20converted%20to%20Buddhism%20and%20never%20climbed%20the%20steps%20of%20any%20Hindu%20temple%2C%20for%20he%20had%20felt%20enslaved%20by%20the%20religion%20to%20follow%20an%20undignified%20caste%20occupation.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20his%20son%2C%20one%20of%20my%20uncles%2C%20who%20as%20a%20young%20man%20was%20denied%20training%20in%20sitar%20playing%2C%20changed%20his%20last%20name%20and%20severed%20his%20family%20ties%20to%20live%20a%20life%20of%20anonymity.%20To%20us%20he%20was%20a%20lost%20one%2C%20living%20in%20hiding.%20Later%2C%20we%20saw%20the%20struggle%20of%20our%20cousin%2C%20the%20son%20of%20my%20uncle%20who%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20fully%20integrate%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98passing%E2%80%99%20upper%20caste%20and%20eventually%20converted%20back%20to%20Buddhism.%20No%20one%20can%20say%20my%20uncle%20or%20his%20kids%20had%20it%20better%20by%20%E2%80%98passing%E2%80%99%20as%20upper%20castes.%20As%20an%20oppressed%20caste%2C%20we%20have%20around%20us%20many%20such%20stories.%20Dutt%20wrote%20her%20story%20in%20full%20honesty%2C%20she%20did%20not%20expect%20applause%20for%20it%2C%20she%20wanted%20to%20feel%20part%20of%20the%20fervour%20that%20had%20begun%20post%20Rohith%20Vemula%E2%80%99s%20death%20which%20was%20bigger%20than%20any%20of%20us.%20She%20didn%E2%80%99t%20expect%20the%20amount%20of%20hatred%20and%20erasure%20that%20came%20her%20way%20either%2C%20for%20not%20being%20the%20ideal%20image%20of%20a%20Dalit%2C%20for%20there%20is%20none!%20I%20cannot%20highlight%20enough%2C%20that%20Dalits%20are%20a%20diverse%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApte%E2%80%99s%20character%20bore%20so%20many%20similarities%20to%20real-life%20Dutt%2C%20that%20dismissing%20her%20demand%20for%20credits%20publicly%20in%20a%20collective%20statement%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20land%20well%20for%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20show.%20The%20dismissive%20collective%20statement%20also%20shows%20who%20wields%20disproportionate%20power%20in%20building%20narratives%20or%20erasing%20them.%20The%20dismissal%20came%20after%20Ghaywan%20acknowledged%20Dutt%20in%20his%20Instagram%20note.%20Since%20there%20was%20an%20informal%20acknowledgement%2C%20there%20should%20have%20been%20formal%20credits%20too.%20It%20is%20about%20ethics%20and%20principles%20of%20engagement.%20Ghaywan%20also%20named%20books%20of%20a%20few%20authors%20which%20came%20to%20their%20aid%20in%20shaping%20the%20story%20of%20the%20episode.%20In%20academic%20practice%2C%20if%20you%20quote%20something%20without%20formal%20acknowledgement%2C%20it%20is%20called%20plagiarism.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20creative%20content%20and%20writing%2C%20it%20is%20a%20copyright%20breach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EMidday%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20makers%20were%20prompt%20to%20pat%20their%20own%20back%20for%20taking%20a%20whole%20day%20to%20talk%20with%20and%20learn%20from%20Ghaywan%E2%80%99s%20experiences%20to%20create%20the%20episode%20in%20question.%20If%20the%20makers%2C%20most%20of%20them%20savarna%20women%2C%20wanted%20to%20truly%20engage%20with%20the%20issues%20of%20caste%20and%20marriage%2C%20a%20one-day%20conversation%20with%20Ghaywan%20would%20only%20mean%20scratching%20the%20surface.%20They%20cannot%20rely%20on%20one%20Dalit%20director%E2%80%99s%20labour%20to%20enlighten%20them%20on%20caste.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20open%20their%20eyes%20to%20the%20fact%20of%20how%20caste%20operates%20around%20them%2C%20how%20they%20are%20complicit.%20They%20will%20have%20to%20bring%20in%20more%20scholars%20and%20creative%20folks%20from%20the%20community%20to%20get%20a%20fuller%20picture.%20They%20can%20then%20happily%20applaud%20their%20creative%20process%20for%20also%20being%20ethical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20literature%20on%20decolonisation%20and%20ethical%20research%20practices%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20case%20of%20indigenous%20communities%20in%20Australia%2C%20New%20Zealand%2C%20Canada%20and%20South%20Africa%2C%20indigenous%20communities%20have%20created%20their%20own%20committees%2C%20protocols%20and%20policies%20for%20researchers%20to%20engage%20with%20them%20in%20a%20respectful%2C%20reciprocative%20and%20collaborative%20manner.%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20we%20demand%20such%20an%20ethical%20practice%20in%20the%20case%20of%20oppressed%20caste%20communities%20and%20tribal%20communities%20in%20India%20and%20extend%20it%20to%20the%20creative%20industry%20too%3F%20It%20was%20very%20easy%20for%20the%20makers%20to%20invite%20a%20few%20scholars%20or%20creative%20writers%2C%20especially%20those%20whose%20works%20inspired%20their%20work%2C%20to%20a%20formal%20consultation.%20It%20is%20about%20the%20ethics%20of%20acknowledgement.%20Oppressed%20caste%20knowledge%20and%20creative%20endeavours%20are%20not%20free%20to%20take.%20They%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20brushed%20aside%20or%20lumped%20together%20as%20the%20experiences%20of%20thousands.%20A%20note%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20episode%20or%20the%20end%2C%20could%20have%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CFor%20our%20storyline%20and%20characters%20we%20credit%20so%20and%20so%20individuals%2C%20whom%20we%20consulted%2C%20compensated%20fairly%20and%20drew%20inspiration%20from.%20Also%2C%20we%20acknowledge%20that%20in%20our%20society%20caste%20has%20a%20big%20significance%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20matrimony%20among%20other%20issues%2C%20and%20this%20story%20also%20draws%20from%20the%20experiences%20of%20thousands%20who%20are%20breaking%20the%20barriers%20of%20caste.%E2%80%9D%20This%20could%20have%20been%20an%20example%20of%20ethical%20acknowledgement%20and%20collaborative%20practice.%20Would%20it%20have%20delayed%20their%20creative%20process%3F%20Well%2C%20it%20would%20certainly%20have%20brought%20out%20a%20more%20enriched%20creative%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnge-Marie%20Hancock%2C%20a%20Black%20scholar%2C%20wrote%20a%20book%20in%202016%20on%20intersectionality%2C%20to%20map%20and%20trace%20the%20genealogy%20of%20intersectionality-like%20thoughts%20and%20to%20lengthen%20the%20concept%E2%80%99s%20historical%20arc.%20She%20aptly%20notes%20that%20Kimberl%C3%A9%20Crenshaw%20and%20Patricial%20Hill%20Collins%20used%20similar%20language%20that%20sounded%20like%20intersectionality-like%20thoughts%20despite%20being%20from%20two%20distinct%20fields.%20She%20states%2C%20that%20if%20one%20were%20to%20argue%20that%20Crenshaw%20and%20Collins%20simultaneously%20(but%20not%20collaboratively)%20founded%20intersectionality%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20then%20what%20shared%20sources%20did%20they%20have%3F%20Hancock%20answers%20this%20question%20by%20tracing%20intersectionality%E2%80%99s%20origins%20to%20activism.%20Because%20intersectionality-like%20thoughts%20and%20language%20existed%20in%20the%20activism%20lexicon%20and%20praxis%2C%20it%20also%20percolated%20in%20academia%2C%20among%20the%20scholars%20who%20described%20or%20did%20intersectionality%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20not%20knowing%20of%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20works.%20I%20state%20this%20source%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20debate%20around%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98Coming%20Out%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDutt%20used%20a%20discourse%20that%20exists%20in%20LGBTQI%2B%20movements%2C%20on%20%E2%80%98coming%20out%E2%80%99%20to%20embrace%20their%20truth.%20Dutt%20extended%20this%20framing%20to%20the%20experience%20of%20thousands%20of%20aspiring%20oppressed%20castes%20who%20choose%20to%20change%20their%20family%20name%20to%20escape%20blatant%20casteism.%20Dutt%E2%80%99s%20work%20validated%20their%20struggle.%20It%20resonated%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDutt%20has%20stated%20in%20several%20of%20her%20interviews%20and%20writings%20that%20followed%20her%20book%2C%20that%20her%20usage%20of%20%E2%80%98coming%20out%E2%80%99%20itself%20is%20not%20radical%2C%20the%20term%20resonated%20with%20her%2C%20but%20her%20using%20the%20discourse%20to%20write%20her%20unique%20narrative%20is%20her%20contribution.%20Against%20the%20backlash%20she%20received%20from%20all%20corners%2C%20she%20continued%20to%20engage%20in%20conversation%20on%20this%20discourse%20that%20she%20has%20built%20over%20the%20years.%20Yet%20the%20makers%20in%20their%20collective%20statement%20brought%20into%20question%20her%20writing%20and%20intellectual%20work%20that%20is%20available%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20by%20questioning%20the%20originality.%20They%20cited%20queer%20Dalit%20academic%20Sumit%20Baudh%E2%80%99s%202007%20article%20which%20is%20not%20available%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20to%20state%20that%20he%20used%20%E2%80%98coming%20out%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20caste%20context%20first.%20After%20the%20collective%20statement%20of%20the%20makers%20came%20out%2C%20Baudh%20went%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20to%20question%20Dutt%2C%20asking%20why%20she%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20credited%20him%20in%20her%20book%20for%20this%20article.%20He%20had%20ample%20time%20since%202019%20to%20ask%20this%20question%20to%20Dutt%2C%20especially%20when%20he%20had%20also%20shared%20panels%20with%20her%20as%20late%20as%20April%202023.%20This%20is%20an%20example%20of%20savarna%20instrumentalising%20one%20oppressed%20caste%20person%20to%20bring%20down%20another.%20Instead%20of%20questioning%20the%20makers%20for%20their%20unethical%20ways%2C%20sadly%20Baudh%20turned%20to%20discredit%20Dutt%20viciously.%20In%20such%20a%20power%20play%2C%20meaningful%20solidarities%20within%20the%20oppressed%20caste%20are%20fractured%2C%20sometimes%20beyond%20repair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20completely%20plausible%20that%20Baudh%20and%20Dutt%20used%20the%20framing%20of%20%E2%80%98coming%20out%E2%80%99%20without%20knowing%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20because%20the%20language%20and%20discourse%20already%20existed%20in%20the%20activist%20community%2C%20which%20does%20not%20take%20away%20the%20labour%20both%20put%20into%20bringing%20forth%20their%20narratives.%20By%20pitting%20Dutt%2C%20Baudh%20and%20to%20some%20extent%20Ghaywan%20against%20each%20other%2C%20the%20savarna%20makers%20have%20pushed%20aside%20their%20own%20responsibility%20of%20self-retrospection%20and%20commitment%20to%20create%20stories%20%E2%80%98bigger%20than%20themselves%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20they%20claim.%20This%20shows%20that%20the%20savarna%2C%20privileged%20caste%20and%20class%20content%20creators%20and%20filmmakers%20are%20not%20yet%20capable%20of%20ethical%20collaborative%20practice%20and%20representation%20of%20the%20marginalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESwati%20Kamble%20is%20an%20anti-caste%20intersectional%20feminist%20researcher-activist.%20Her%20research%20broadly%20focuses%20on%20human%20rights%20and%20social%20justice%20movements%2C%20decolonisation%20and%20intersectionality.%20She%20has%20a%20PhD%20in%20socio-economics%20from%20the%20faculty%20of%20social%20sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Geneva.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693039516000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fw