k%2Farticleshow%2F103054900.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20New%20Appointments%20to%20CIC%20Despite%20Government%20Receiving%20256%20Applications%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Though%20the%20Union%20government%C2%A0received%20256%20applications%20for%20the%20posts%20of%20information%20commissioners%20in%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%20(CIC)%2C%20no%20appointments%20have%20been%20made%20in%20eight%20months%20to%20fill%20up%20vacancies%20in%20the%20statutory%20body%20which%20is%20already%20working%20below%20half%20its%20capacity.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20all%20the%20incumbent%20commissioners%20are%20set%20to%20demit%20office%20by%20the%20end%20of%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20information%20was%20revealed%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2024%2C%20in%20response%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20query%20filed%20by%20Commodore%20(Retired)%20Lokesh%20Batra.%20In%20December%202022%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20and%20Training%20(DoPT)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fgovt-invites-applications-for-information-commissioners-in-cic-news-246971%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E%20eligible%20applicants%20to%20apply%20for%20the%20posts%20of%20information%20commissioners%20(not%20exceeding%20six).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deadline%20for%20application%20was%20January%2012%2C%202023%2C%20by%20which%20time%20the%20DoPT%20received%20256%20applications.%20In%20addition%2C%2012%20persons%20sent%20their%20applications%20after%20the%20deadline%20had%20passed.%20Though%20eight%20months%20have%20passed%20since%20the%20deadline%2C%20no%20appointments%20have%20been%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20Commodore%20Batra%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20query%2C%20the%20DoPT%20gave%20details%20of%20the%20search%20and%20selection%20process%20and%20that%20the%20particulars%20of%20applicants%20were%20tabulated%20by%20it%20and%20sent%20to%20a%20search%20committee%20constituted%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20headed%20by%20the%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EGovt%20got%20256%20applications%20for%20posts%20of%20information%20commissioners%20at%20CIC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENames%20of%20256%20Applicants%20for%20ICs%20-Advt%20dt%2020.12.2022%20%2B%3Cbr%3E%5Cnnames%20of%2012%20late%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20we%20know%20any%20one%20of%20the%20name%20in%20the%20list%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20RTI%20Response.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FSRleYUCDc0%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FSRleYUCDc0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20CommodoreLokeshBatra%20(%40CommodoreBatra)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCommodoreBatra%2Fstatus%2F1695328014610190506%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2026%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppointments%20are%20finalised%20by%20a%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20comprising%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister.%20The%20persons%20who%20are%20recommended%20by%20the%20committee%20are%20appointed%20to%20the%20CIC%20by%20the%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CIC%20is%20the%20highest%20appellate%20authority%20in%20RTI%20matters%20concerning%20the%20Union%20government.%20As%20against%20the%20total%20strength%20of%20one%20chief%20information%20commissioner%20and%20ten%20information%20commissioners%2C%20it%20is%20functioning%20with%20one%20chief%20information%20commissioner%20and%20four%20information%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tenure%20of%20chief%20information%20commissioner%20Y.K.%20Sinha%20will%20end%20on%20October%203.%20The%20remaining%20information%20commissioners%20%E2%80%94%20Suresh%20Chandra%2C%20Uday%20Mahurkar%2C%20Heeralal%20Samariya%20and%20Saroj%20Punhani%20%E2%80%94%20will%20leave%20office%20in%20November%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fgovt-got-256-applications-for-posts-of-information-commissioners-at-cic-reveals-rti-reply%2F1729320%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520its%2520response%2520to%2520an%2Ccommissioners%2520(not%2520exceeding%2520six).%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20news%20agency%20PTI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERTI%20activists%20have%20long%20protested%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20attempts%20to%20dilute%20the%20landmark%20transparency%20law.%20The%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%20passed%20in%20the%20recently%20concluded%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20will%20further%20reduce%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%20activists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fregressive-amendments-to-rti-act-ncpri-flags-concerns-over-digital-personal-data-protection-bill%5C%22%3Ehave%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Recently%2C%20years%20of%20information%20stored%20on%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20portal%20for%20RTI%20applications%20%E2%80%9Cdisappeared%E2%80%9D%20suddenly.%20After%20activists%20raised%20an%20alarm%2C%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frti-portal-rtionline-years-of-information-disappears%5C%22%3Eclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20website%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20maintenance%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Carchival%20data%20will%20be%20available%20soon%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693038542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcic-applications-no-new-appointments%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20advertisement%20was%20issued%20to%20fill%20up%20vacancies%20in%20the%20statutory%20body%20eight%20months%20ago.%20The%20Central%20Information%20Commission%20is%20already%20working%20below%20half%20its%20capacity%20and%20all%20the%20incumbent%20commissioners%20are%20set%20to%20demit%20office%20by%20the%20end%20of%20November.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcic-applications-no-new-appointments%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tamil%20Nadu%20Extends%20Acclaimed%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20to%2029%2C463%20More%20Schools%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121001%2FBreakfast-scheme-in-Chennai-2-750x500-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20extended%20its%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20for%20primary%20students%20to%2029%2C463%20more%20schools%20on%20Friday%2C%20August%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20will%20now%20serve%20nutritious%20breakfast%20to%2017%20lakh%20students%20from%20Classes%20I%20to%20V%20studying%20in%2031%2C008%20schools%20at%20an%20annual%20cost%20of%20Rs%20404.41%20crore.%20Launched%20on%20September%2015%2C%202022%2C%20the%20scheme%20initially%20covered%201%2C14%2C095%20students%20in%201%2C545%20schools%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%2033.56%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20minister%20M.K.%20Stalin%20launched%20the%20extension%20of%20the%20scheme%20at%20Tirukkuvalai%20in%20Nagapattinam%2C%20where%20his%20father%20and%20former%20chief%20minister%20M.%20Karunanidhi%20had%20studied.%20Stalin%20also%20shared%20the%20meal%20with%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20expanded%20the%20scheme%20considering%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20preliminary%20phase%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20aim%20is%20to%20ensure%20children%20attend%20school%20without%20hunger%20and%C2%A0prevent%20malnutrition%2C%20achieve%20average%20height%20in%20children%2C%20prevent%20underweight%20in%20adolescents%2C%20prevent%20anemia%20and%20vitamin%20B12%20deficiency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStalin%20had%20invited%20elected%20representatives%20to%20launch%20the%20plan%E2%80%99s%20extension%20in%20a%20government%20primary%20school%20in%20their%20respective%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EVIDEO%20%7C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20CM%20MK%20Stalin%20enjoys%20a%20meal%20with%20school%20children%20in%20Nagapattinam%20district%20as%20he%20launched%20the%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20breakfast%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20initially%20launched%20to%20provide%20breakfast%20to%20over%201%20lakh%20students%20in%20classes%201%20to%205%20across%201%2C545%20government%20schools%2C%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FAc7KBSI4uF%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FAc7KBSI4uF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20(%40PTI_News)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1694908221876531270%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2025%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmiles%20all%20around%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20minister%20Ma%20Subramanian%20inaugurated%20the%20programme%20at%20the%20Chennai%20Primary%20School%20at%20Manthope%20in%20Saidapet.%20As%20many%20as%201%2C075%20students%20of%20the%20school%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20stated%20that%20each%20student%20will%20be%20served%20cereals%20like%20semolina%2C%20wheat%2C%20rice%2C%20millet%2C%20and%20pulses%2C%20and%20locally%20available%20vegetables%20from%20Monday%20to%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20will%20be%20provided%20150%20to%20200%20grams%20of%20cooked%20food%20and%2060%20grams%20of%20sambar%20with%20vegetables.%20This%20is%20apart%20from%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20provided%20to%20students%20till%20Class%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES%20Paul%20Raj%2C%20a%20fifth-grade%20student%20at%20Chennai%20Primary%20School%20in%20Saidapet%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20boy%20used%20to%20attend%20school%20on%20an%20empty%20stomach%2C%20since%20his%20mother%20has%20to%20leave%20for%20work%20early%20and%20family%20has%20limited%20resources.%20On%20Friday%2C%20his%20face%20lit%20up%20when%20the%20school%20bell%20rang%2C%20announcing%20the%20breakfast%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaj%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20he%20had%20a%20satisfying%20meal%20of%20khichdi%2C%20sambar%20and%20kesari.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20I%20would%20be%20famished%20by%2011%20am%20and%20eagerly%20wait%20for%20the%20bell%20to%20ring%20to%20have%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20provided%20at%20the%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20child%20grinned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMore%20than%2070%25%20of%20the%20students%20do%20not%20have%20breakfast%20at%20home.%20We%20were%20happy%20that%20the%20students%20enjoyed%20the%20breakfast.%20No%20one%20wasted%20the%20food.%20The%20dull%2C%20inactive%20faces%20of%20the%20children%20lit%20up%20with%20happiness%2C%E2%80%9D%20V.%20Umaparvathy%20at%20the%20Saidapet%20school%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1.jpeg%20750w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1-300x150.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669962%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESchoolchildren%20being%20served%20breakfast.%20Photo%3A%20Laasya%20Shekhar%2FSouth%20First%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EImproved%20attendance%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20positive%20impact%20of%20this%20programme%20extends%20far%20beyond%20filling%20empty%20stomachs.%20A%20recent%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20State%20Planning%20Commission%20found%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20attendance%20among%20government%20schools%20implementing%20the%20breakfast%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20out%20of%20the%201%2C543%20schools%20where%20children%20have%20been%20receiving%20breakfast%20since%2015%20September%2C%202022%2C%201%2C319%20schools%20witnessed%20a%20remarkable%20rise%20in%20attendance%20during%20January%20and%20February%2C%20compared%20to%20June-July%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20base%20attendance%20data%20of%20the%20initial%201%2C543%20beneficiary%20schools%20was%20compared%20against%20that%20of%20neighbouring%20schools%20within%201-2%20km%20by%20considering%20the%20geographical%20coordinates%20of%20the%20schools%2C%20reported%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ffree-breakfast-scheme-has-improved-attendance-in-schools-tamil-nadu-govt-study-1200572.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20considered%20only%20schools%20with%20enrolment%20of%2025%20and%20above%20and%20schools%20with%20consistent%20attendance%20reporting%20above%2075%25.%20This%20left%20the%20study%20with%2072%20beneficiary%20schools%20each%20mapped%20with%20at%20least%20two%20to%2015%20neighbouring%20schools%2C%20which%20took%20the%20total%20to%20414.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuick%20rewind%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20many%20pioneering%20schemes%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20providing%20food%20to%20the%20school%20children%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20an%20initiative%20that%20improved%20the%20attendance%20and%20reduced%20malnutrition%20among%20socially%20struggling%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1920%3A%20The%20then%20Mayor%20of%20Chennai%20Corporation%2C%20Sir%20PT%20Thiyagarayar%2C%20passed%20a%20resolution%20to%20implement%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20in%20Corporation%20School%20at%20Thousand%20Lights%2C%20Chennai.%20The%20scheme%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20school%E2%80%99s%20student%20strength.%20The%20scheme%20was%20expanded%20to%20a%20few%20more%20schools%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1947%3A%20Due%20to%20financial%20constraints%2C%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20was%20abandoned%2C%20except%20in%20Harijan%20Welfare%20Department-run%20schools.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1957%3A%20Chief%20minister%20K%20Kamaraj%20resumed%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20for%20primary%20school%20students.%20%E2%82%B910%20lakh%20was%20allotted%20for%20implementing%20this%20scheme%2C%20with%20a%20clause%20that%20it%20should%20not%20exceeding%20%E2%82%B918%20per%20child%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1982%3A%20Chief%20minister%20MG%20Ramachandran%20introduced%20the%20Nutritious%20Meal%20Programme.%20Children%20in%20pre-school%20and%20primary%20schools%20were%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1989%3A%C2%A0%20Chief%20minister%20M%20Karunanidhi%20included%20an%20egg%20every%20two%20weeks%20to%20the%20menu%20of%20the%20nutritious%20meal%20scheme.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1998-2008%3A%20The%20egg%20count%20gradually%20increased%20from%20one%20per%20week%20to%20three%20per%20week.%20The%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20provided%20bananas%20for%20the%20children%20who%20would%20not%20eat%20eggs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E2010%3A%20Egg%20count%20goes%20to%20five%20every%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Ftamilnadu%2Ftn-extends-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools-brings-cheer-to-17-lakh-primary-students%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20South%20First.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693036826000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121001%2FBreakfast-scheme-in-Chennai-2-750x500-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftamil-nadu-extends-acclaimed-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Chief%20Minister's%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20provides%20breakfast%20to%20primary%20school%20children%2C%20addressing%20hunger%20and%20improving%20attendance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Ftamil-nadu-extends-acclaimed-breakfast-scheme-to-29463-more-schools%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20moon%20landing%2C%20Isro%20eyes%20Sept%202%20for%20launch%20of%20Aditya-L1%20solar%20mission%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693036050000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F18%2Ffull%2F1692342631-0275.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fafter-moon-landing-isro-eyes-sept-2-for-launch-of-aditya-l1-solar-mission-123082600340_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20the%20successful%20moon%20lander%20venture%2C%20ISRO%20is%20now%20gearing%20up%20for%20the%20launch%20of%2