22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Trading%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fgovernment%2Frevdi-culture-welfare-narendra-modi%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edebt%20concern%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20needs%20closer%20attention.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Union%20government%20spending%20is%20proliferating%20(as%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20GDP)%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-state-fiscal-freedom-abritrary-squeezing%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20government%20continues%20to%20squeeze%20the%20fiscal%20autonomy%20and%20borrowing%20capacity%20of%20the%20states%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(particularly%20those%20with%20an%20opposition%20government%20in%20power)%2C%20the%20overall%20external%20debt%20borrowings%20and%20the%20government%20debt%20to%20GDP%20numbers%20are%20a%20cause%20of%20concern.%20It%20not%20only%20raises%20questions%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98effectiveness%E2%80%99%20of%20a%20pre-designed%20fiscal%20consolidation%20plan%20but%20also%20on%20the%20viability%20of%20the%20BJP%20government%E2%80%99s%20spending%20or%20outlayed%20preferences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20may%20continue%20to%20see%20the%20Union%20government%20spend%20more%20on%20PLI%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fgovernment%2Frevdi-culture-welfare-narendra-modi%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Espending%20less%20on%20welfare%20programmes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20nutrition%20schemes%20and%20other%20social%20capital%20needs%20like%20healthcare%20and%20educational%20spending.%20But%20with%20a%20rising%20government%20debt%20concern%20(when%20growth%20is%20low)%2C%20the%20fiscal%20space%20for%20the%20government%20to%20do%20more%20%E2%80%93%20both%20on%20capex%20and%20welfare%20%E2%80%93%20ma